comment.author: 41909278@N08
comment._content:
This is, in fact the NA-16-4M, other wise known as the NA-31*, one of two pattern ships sold to Sweden, where the aircraft was built under licence as the ASJA (later SAAB) Sk 14. The other pattern ship, the NA-38, which was identical, was test flown and dismantled for shipment. 

*North American Aviation used two numbers, usually different, for each order they filled. One was their accounting number, the other a customer identifier.

Doug MacPhail
